The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, December 12, 2003 				 Feedback on supervision 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Dec. 11: The Reserve Bank, in its bid to be an efficient supervisor, is planning to introduce a system of feedback on its supervision from banks on a regular basis. 																								RBI governor Y. V. Reddy said the rating will help improve the quality of supervision and will also result in overall reduction of transaction costs.																								There are some suggestions that the supervision should be improved. We will ask you to rate our supervision. Self regulatory organisations will be consulted, he said at the 25th Bank Economists Conference today. 																								Reddy added that the central bank will soon be preparing a proforma for feedback. 																								He added that the RBI will also simplify its draft circulars.																								Another aspect are circulars. Some have pointed out that they are complex. Even I have found them difficult to understand, he said. 																								The plan is now to prepare, in consultation with self regulatory organisations, a users panel consisting of those in charge of compliance in the regulated institutions.
